MAP
  Display an ASCII map of explored territory.

SYNTAX
  map  [<sects>]
  bmap [<sects>]
  smap [<sects>]

DESCRIPTION
  Draws a map of the given area.  Each cell shows the sector's
  designation character.  Sectors you own show their type letter
  (c=capital, a=agri, g=gold, h=harbor, etc).  Unknown terrain
  shows '?'.  Sea is '.', mountains are '^'.

  All three variants (map/bmap/smap) behave identically.

  Hex grid directions from any sector:
         y  u
          \ /
     g ---[ ]--- j
          / \
         b   n
  u=upper-right  j=right  n=lower-right
  b=lower-left   g=left   y=upper-left

EXAMPLE
  map *                     full explored world
  map -10:10,-10:10         20-wide view around capital
  map 0,0:5                 5 sectors out from capital

